      "writtenOn": "2019-02-28T18:15:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The advantage is reducing repetitive typing in case many verifiers are declared inline, e.g.\n\nluci.cq_group(\n   verifiers \u003d [\n       luci.cq_tryjob_verifier(builder \u003d \u0027B1\u0027),\n       luci.cq_tryjob_verifier(builder \u003d \u0027B2\u0027),\n       luci.cq_tryjob_verifier(builder \u003d \u0027B3\u0027),\n       luci.cq_tryjob_verifier(builder \u003d \u0027B4\u0027),\n   ]\n)\n\nbecomes:\n\nluci.cq_group(\n   verifiers \u003d [\n       {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B1\u0027},\n       {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B2\u0027},\n       {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B3\u0027},\n       {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B4\u0027},\n   ]\n)\n\nIn case you asking \"why not just allow string alias, but forbid dict alias\" the answer is: to be consistent with luci.console_view which is structurally similar and it allows dict, because there they are more important to reduce \n\nluci.console_view(\n    entries \u003d [\n        luci.console_view_entry(\n            builder \u003d \u0027B1\u0027,\n            short_name \u003d \u0027b1\u0027,\n            category \u003d \u0027b|b1\u0027,\n        ),\n        luci.console_view_entry(\n            builder \u003d \u0027B2\u0027,\n            short_name \u003d \u0027b2\u0027,\n            category \u003d \u0027b|b2\u0027,\n        ),\n        luci.console_view_entry(\n            builder \u003d \u0027B3\u0027,\n            short_name \u003d \u0027b3\u0027,\n            category \u003d \u0027b|b3\u0027,\n        ),\n        luci.console_view_entry(\n            builder \u003d \u0027B3\u0027,\n            short_name \u003d \u0027b3\u0027,\n            category \u003d \u0027b|b3\u0027,\n        ),\n    ],\n)\n\nto \n\nluci.console_view(\n    entries \u003d [\n        {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B1\u0027, \u0027short_name\u0027: \u0027b1\u0027, \u0027category\u0027: \u0027b|b1\u0027},\n        {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B2\u0027, \u0027short_name\u0027: \u0027b2\u0027, \u0027category\u0027: \u0027b|b2\u0027},\n        {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B3\u0027, \u0027short_name\u0027: \u0027b3\u0027, \u0027category\u0027: \u0027b|b3\u0027},\n        {\u0027builder\u0027: \u0027B4\u0027, \u0027short_name\u0027: \u0027b4\u0027, \u0027category\u0027: \u0027b|b4\u0027},\n    ],\n)\n\nWhy do you think it will be confusing? It is like assigning dicts to proto messages fields in python (it auto-instantiates corresponding messages from them).",
